author: COMSOL
description:
Periodic microstructures are frequently found in composite materials, metallic foams, and sandwich structures. They can be represented by a unit cell repeated along the three cartesian directions.

This app computes homogenized material properties of various periodic microstructures and makes them available in an MPH- or an XML-file that can subsequently be imported into a COMSOL Multiphysics session.

Ten different microstructures represented by periodic unit cells are available. The cell dimensions and the constituent materials are modifiable by the user. The app calculates the homogenized density, elasticity matrix, coefficient of thermal expansion, heat capacity, and thermal conductivity of the unit cell, which thereafter can be used in a macroscopic model.
label: homogenization_of_periodic_microstructures.mph

commentsinfile
settings.value:
Unidirectional Fiber Composite, Square Packing

A cell with circular fiber surrounded by a matrix. The fiber is placed at the center of the cell longitudinal cross section. Instead of a fiber domain, an internal void can be created to model a microchannel.

Either specify fiber diameter and cell dimensions or fiber volume fraction and cell dimensions.

settings.name: commentsinfile
settings.value:
Unidirectional Fiber Composite, Hexagonal Packing

A cell with circular fibers surrounded by a matrix. One fiber is placed at the center, and quarter fibers are placed at the corners of the cell longitudinal cross section.

Either specify fiber diameter and cell dimensions or fiber volume fraction and cell dimensions.

settings.name: commentsinfile
settings.value:
Bidirectional Fiber Composite

A cell with circular fibers surrounded by a matrix. One fiber is placed at the center of the cell longitudinal cross section, and quarter fibers are placed at the corners of the cell lateral cross section.

Either specify fiber diameter and cell dimensions or fiber volume fraction and cell dimensions.

settings.name: commentsinfile
settings.value:
Bidirectional Non-Crimp Fiber Composite

A cell with straight fiber strands in the longitudinal and lateral directions embedded in a matrix.

settings.name: commentsinfile
settings.value:
Bidirectional Plain Weave Fiber Composite

A cell with fiber strands in a plain weave embedded in a matrix. The fiber strands can have an elliptical or circular cross section.

settings.name: commentsinfile
settings.value:
Particulate Composite, Primitive Cubic

A cell with a spherical particle surrounded by a matrix. The spherical particle is placed at the center of the matrix. Instead of a particle, an internal void can be created to model a foam structure.

Either specify particle diameter and cell dimensions or particle volume fraction and cell dimensions.

settings.name: commentsinfile
settings.value:
Particulate Composite, Body-Centered Cubic

A cell with spherical particles surrounded by a matrix. One spherical particle is placed at the center, and one eighth particles are placed at the corners of the cell.

Either specify particle diameter and cell dimensions or particle volume fraction and cell dimensions.

settings.name: commentsinfile
settings.value:
Particulate Composite, Face-Centered Cubic

A cell with spherical particles surrounded by a matrix. Half spherical particles are placed at the center of face, and one eighth particles are placed at the corners of the cell.

Either specify particle diameter and cell dimensions or particle volume fraction and cell dimensions.

settings.name: commentsinfile
settings.value:
Honeycomb, Hexagonal Cross Section

A cell for a honeycomb structure with hexagonal cross section.

settings.name: commentsinfile
settings.value:
Sandwich

A cell for a sandwich structure.
